videos.description: Florida Gulf Coast's Demetris Morant throws down a rim rocking alley-oop.
videos.headline: Dunk City back in style

videos.description: Demetris Morant puts North Florida's Wajid Aminu on a poster with a huge two handed dunk.
videos.headline: Morant says welcome to my poster

videos.description: UNF's Dallas Moore throws down nice fast break dunk.
videos.headline: Ospreys show that they can fly too with big dunk

videos.description: Marc-Eddy Norelia throws down a huge one handed slam in transition.
videos.headline: Norelia finishes with vicious one handed slam

videos.description: Marc-Eddy Norelia throws down a huge putback slam off a missed jumper.
videos.headline: Norelia back at it with huge putback slam

videos.description: Rayjon Tucker throws down massive dunk that shuts off the shot clock.
videos.headline: Tucker stops time with massive dunk

videos.description: Demetris Morant throws down the alley-oop with authority.
videos.headline: Morant throws down powerful alley-oop

videos.description: Christian Terell knocks down the fast break 3-pointer after a huge block from Marc-Eddy Norelia.
videos.headline: FGCU shows they are more than dunks with big block and fast break 3

videos.description: Fans storm the court after Florida Gulf Coast wins the Atlantic Sun Conference Tournament and punch their ticket for the NCAA Tournament.
videos.headline: Dunk City is dancing again

videos.description: FGCU's Brandon Goodwin talks about his teams expectations going into the NCAA Tournament in the post game breakdown
videos.headline: Goodwin believes FGCU is putting it all together at the right time

videos.description: FGCU's Brandon Goodwin receives the Atlantic Sun's Tournament MVP.
videos.headline: Goodwin Atlantic Sun Tournament MVP

videos.description: The trophy presentation to FGCU for winning the Atlantic Sun Conference Tournamnet.
videos.headline: FGCU receives Atlantic Sun Tournament trophy

videos.description: All five Florida Gulf Coast starters score in double figures with several highlight-reel dunks in a 77-61 victory against North Florida in the championship game of the Atlantic Sun tournament.

videos.headline: Dunk City captures second straight A-Sun title
